09/01/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police have arrested a Croatian citizen wanted by Serbia for war crimes against civilians, BiH Court Spokesperson Selma Hadzic confirmed on Thursday (January 6th). 
Tihomir Purda, 42, from Vukovar, was detained on Wednesday at the border with Croatia while attempting to enter BiH. 
A BiH court remanded him to 18 days in custody pending extradition. 
(Nezavisne Novine - 07/01/11; Tanjug, Hina - 06/01/11)
